@node Adjust Filename, Combination with ebzip, Select Subbooks, Invoking ebrefile
@section Adjust Filename

@code{ebrefile} keeps @dfn{case} (upper or lower) and @dfn{suffix} of
the original catalog file.
When the catalog filename is @file{catalogs;1} (case is lower, and suffix
is @samp{;1}), @code{ebrefile} puts a new catalog file as
@file{catalogs;1}, and backup the original catalog file as
@file{catalogs.bak;1}.

The following table displayes how a filename of @file{CATALOG(S)}
file changes.

@multitable @columnfractions .4 .3 .3
@item case/suffix       @tab original file      @tab backup file
@item lower/none        @tab catalog            @tab catalog.bak
@item lower/dot         @tab catalog.           @tab catalog.bak
@item lower/version     @tab catalog;1          @tab catalog.bak;1
@item lower/dot+version @tab catalog.;1         @tab catalog.bak;1
@item upper/none        @tab CATALOG            @tab CATALOG.BAK
@item upper/dot         @tab CATALOG.           @tab CATALOG.BAK
@item upper/version     @tab CATALOG;1          @tab CATALOG.BAK;1
@item upper/dot+version @tab CATALOG.;1         @tab CATALOG.BAK;1
@end multitable

The @samp{--case} and @samp{--suffix} options allows you to modify
these case and suffix styles of new catalog file and backup file.
The @samp{--case} option takes an argument, and it must be @samp{upper}
or @samp{lower}.
The option sets the case of the filename @code{CATALOG(S)} and 
@code{CATALOG(S).BAK} to upper or lower.
Also the @samp{--suffix} option takes an argument, and it must be
@samp{none}, @samp{dot}, @samp{version} or @samp{both}.
The option sets the suffix style of the filename @code{CATALOG(S)}
and @code{CATALOG(S).BAK} to none, dot, version or both (dot+version).

