@node Summary of Options,  , Invoking ebrefile, Top
@chapter Summary of @code{ebrefile} Options

The @code{ebrefile} command supports both traditional single-letter
options and mnemonic long option names.
Long option names are indicated with @samp{--} instead of @samp{-}.
Abbreviations for option names are allowed as long as they are unique.

@table @code
@item -c @var{case}
@itemx --case @var{case}
Output a catalog file which have filenames with upper or lower @var{case}
letters.
@var{case} must be @samp{upper} or @samp{lower}.
When this option is not specified, the case of the new catalog filename
comes to be the same as a filename of orignal catalog file.
(@xref{Adjust Filename}, for more details).

@item -h
@itemx --help
Output help message to standard out, then exit.

@item -o @var{directory}
@itemx --output-directory @var{directory}
Output a new catalog file under @var{directory}.
By default, @code{ebrefile} generates a new catalog file under the
current working directory (@code{.}).
(@xref{Invoking ebrefile}, for more details).

@item -s @var{suffix}
@itemx --suffix @var{suffix}
Specify the suffix of filename of new catalog file.
@var{suffix} must be @samp{none}, @samp{dot}, @samp{version} or @samp{both}.
When @var{suffix} is @samp{none}, no suffix is appended.
When @var{suffix} is @samp{dot}, a dot (@samp{.}) is appended.
When @var{suffix} is @samp{version}, a version number 1 (@samp{;1}) is
appended.
When @var{suffix} is @samp{both}, dot and version number 1 (@samp{.;1})
is appended.
If this option is not specified, the suffix of the new catalog filename
comes to be the same as a filename of original catalog file.
(@xref{Adjust Filename}, for more details).

@item -S @var{subbooks}
@itemx --subbook @var{subbooks}
Specify subbooks which @code{ebrefile} imports to a new catalog file.
@var{subbooks} must be a list of directory names of subbooks separeted
by a comma (@samp{,}).
By default, all subbooks are specified as target.
(@xref{Select Subbooks}, for more details).

@item -v
@itemx --version
Output version number to standard out, then exit.
@end table

